116,"watchers":42996,"default_branch":"main","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevyengine/bevy/pulls/15480","html_url":"https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/pull/15480","diff_url":"https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/pull/15480.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/pull/15480.patch","merged_at":"2024-10-03T16:38:40Z"},"body":"# Objective\r\n\r\nFixes #14511.\r\n\r\n`despawn` allows you to remove entities from the world. However, if the entity does not exist, it emits a warning. This may not be intended behavior for many users who have use cases where they need to call `despawn` regardless of if the entity actually exists (see the issue), or don't care in general if the entity already doesn't exist.\r\n\r\n(Also trying to gauge interest on if this feature makes sense, I'd personally love to have it, but I could see arguments that this might be a footgun. Just trying to help here ðŸ˜„ If there's no contention I could also implement this for `despawn_recursive` and `despawn_descendants` in the same PR)\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nAdd `try_despawn`, `try_despawn_recursive` and `try_despawn_descendants`.\r\n\r\nModify `World::despawn_with_caller` to also take in a `warn` boolean argument, which is then considered when logging the warning. Set `log_warning` to `true` in the case of `despawn`, and `false` in the case of `try_despawn`.\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n\r\nRan `cargo run -p ci` on macOS, it seemed fine.\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevyengine/bevy/issues/15480/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevyengine/bevy/issues/15480/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"id":14507312878,"node_id":"REFE_lADODf6-U86RFY7fzwAAAANgtAbu","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevye